# ============================================================================
# Personal Finance API — Demo flow (VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client)
# ============================================================================
#
# Run the requests TOP TO BOTTOM. Responses are chained via named requests
# (`# @name xxx` → `{{xxx.response.body.field}}`), so order matters.
#
# What this flow demonstrates (the interesting parts of the API):
#   1.  Auth: register → login → JWT pair
#   2.  Domain rules: budget as a hard gate (422 when an expense would exceed it)
#   3.  Invariant protection: budget can't be deleted (409) nor lowered below
#       what was already spent (409) while expenses exist in the period
#   4.  Refresh token rotation + REPLAY DETECTION: reusing a rotated token
#       kills the WHOLE token family (both old and new tokens die)
#
# Environment: switch @baseUrl between local and the live Railway deployment.
# ============================================================================

# -- Live (Railway)
@baseUrl = https://personal-finance-api-production-cbfe.up.railway.app/api/v1
@healthUrl = https://personal-finance-api-production-cbfe.up.railway.app

# -- Local — comment the block above and uncomment this one
# @baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
# @healthUrl = http://localhost:3000

# Demo identity for THIS flow — intentionally different from the seeded
# showcase user (demo-recruiter@finanzas.dev, see scripts/seed-demo.mjs), so
# running the flow never pollutes the curated demo data.
# Re-running the whole file? Bump @email (e.g. demo-flow-2@...) — categories
# are unique per user, so a second run against the same user 409s at step 4.
@email = demo-flow@finanzas.dev
@password = DemoRecruiter2026!

# Period used by budgets/transactions — keep both in the same month.
# @month feeds the budget (integer); @monthPadded feeds ISO dates (2 digits).
@month = 7
@monthPadded = 07
@year = 2026

### 0. Liveness — no auth, excluded from the api/v1 prefix
GET {{healthUrl}}/health

### 1. Register (201 — or 409 on re-run, then just continue with login)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Recruiter",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login → access + refresh pair (200)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Create account (201)
# @name account
POST {{baseUrl}}/accounts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Cuenta Corriente Demo",
  "type": "corriente",
  "initialBalance": 500000
}

### 4. Create income category (201)
# @name catIncome
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Sueldo",
  "nature": "income",
  "color": "#2E7D32"
}

### 5. Create expense category (201)
# @name catExpense
POST {{baseUrl}}/categories
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Supermercado",
  "nature": "expense",
  "color": "#FF5733",
  "icon": "shopping-cart"
}

### 6. Income: salary lands on the account (201) — no budget needed for income
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "accountId": "{{account.response.body.id}}",
  "categoryId": "{{catIncome.response.body.id}}",
  "nature": "income",
  "amount": 800000,
  "description": "Sueldo del mes",
  "transactionDate": "{{year}}-{{monthPadded}}-01"
}

### 7. Create budget for Supermercado: limit 100.000 (201)
# @name budget
POST {{baseUrl}}/budgets
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "categoryId": "{{catExpense.response.body.id}}",
  "month": {{month}},
  "year": {{year}},
  "limit": 100000
}

### 8. Expense within the budget: 60.000 of 100.000 (201)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "accountId": "{{account.response.body.id}}",
  "categoryId": "{{catExpense.response.body.id}}",
  "nature": "expense",
  "amount": 60000,
  "description": "Compra semanal",
  "transactionDate": "{{year}}-{{monthPadded}}-05"
}

### 9. ⛔ Expense that would EXCEED the budget: 60k + 50k > 100k → 422
# The gate runs under a FOR UPDATE lock on the budget row, so even N
# concurrent requests can never overspend the limit (see docs/concurrency-model.md)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "accountId": "{{account.response.body.id}}",
  "categoryId": "{{catExpense.response.body.id}}",
  "nature": "expense",
  "amount": 50000,
  "description": "Esto NO debe pasar el límite",
  "transactionDate": "{{year}}-{{monthPadded}}-12"
}

### 10. ⛔ Delete the budget while it has expenses in the period → 409
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/budgets/{{budget.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 11. ⛔ Lower the limit below what was already spent (60k) → 409
# BudgetLimitBelowSpentException — the sum runs under the budget-row lock
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/budgets/{{budget.response.body.id}}/limit
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

{
  "limit": 50000
}

### 12. Budget state for the period (200) — spent vs limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/budgets?month={{month}}&year={{year}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 13. Account state (200) — balance = 500k + 800k − 60k = 1.240.000
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/{{account.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 14. Rotate the refresh token (200) — the pair from login is now REVOKED
# @name rotated
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{login.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 15. 🔥 REPLAY ATTACK: reuse the ALREADY-ROTATED token → 401
# Replay detection: presenting a revoked token proves the chain is compromised
# (stolen token or client retry — indistinguishable, so we don't try).
# Side effect: the WHOLE token family is revoked, including the new pair.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{login.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 16. 🔥 Proof of family revocation: even the NEW token (step 14) is dead → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{rotated.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

### 17. Recover: login again (200)
# @name relogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 18. Logout: revoke the current refresh token (204)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{relogin.response.body.refreshToken}}"
}

# ============================================================================
# 🎬 Storyboard for the 2-minute demo GIF/video
# ============================================================================
# Record VS Code with this file open, clicking "Send Request" per scene.
#
#  Scene 1 (0:00–0:20)  Requests 1–2. "Register + login: JWT access & refresh."
#  Scene 2 (0:20–0:50)  Requests 3–8. "Account, categories, budget of 100k,
#                        salary in, 60k expense — all 201."
#  Scene 3 (0:50–1:20)  Requests 9–11. The three 4xx in a row: 422 (limit),
#                        409 (delete gated), 409 (lower below spent).
#                        Caption: "the budget row is a mutex — these rules
#                        hold even under concurrent requests."
#  Scene 4 (1:20–1:50)  Requests 14–16. Rotation, then replay → 401, then the
#                        killer detail: the NEW token is also dead (family
#                        revocation). Caption: "replay detection."
#  Scene 5 (1:50–2:00)  Swagger UI at {{healthUrl}}/api/docs — scroll the
#                        endpoint list. "Docs live at /api/docs."
# ============================================================================
